[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, I wanted to ask if there are definitions for when a relation is confluent, Church-Rosser, has the diamond property, and similar properties of relations?<br>\nI have seen that some theorems, for example <code>Relation.church_rosser</code>, use this concepts, but they have inline the definition, so I guess that maybe they are not defined anywhere</p>",
        "id": 562243622,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1765029342
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Might be useful:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/61296f14bcbe0713eecfb377e5776006ae1f95bb/Cslib/Foundations/Data/Relation.lean#L22\"><code>Diamond</code> in CSLib</a></li>\n<li>CSLib proof of <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/61296f14bcbe0713eecfb377e5776006ae1f95bb/Cslib/Languages/CombinatoryLogic/Confluence.lean#L10-L17\">Church-Rosser for SKI calculus</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Danelnov/Lambda-Calculus-Formalization\">https://github.com/Danelnov/Lambda-Calculus-Formalization</a></li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 562253608,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1765041217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, so it is in CSLib, that's why I didn't find it</p>",
        "id": 562253795,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1765041466
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you</p>",
        "id": 562253798,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1765041469
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you know why is this in CSLib instead of Mathlib? Considering that some lemmas in Mathlib (like  <code>Relation.church_rosser</code>) are essentially using them, it is surprising for me that it is not in Mathlib</p>",
        "id": 562253802,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1765041474
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I initially added those (IIRC very early before it was even part of CSLib), simply because Mathlib didn't have them. If people agree they belong upstream, I'm happy to make a PR.</p>",
        "id": 562255335,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Henson",
        "timestamp": 1765043276
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"646655\">Iván Renison</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Confluent.2C.20Church-Rosser.2C.20diamond.2C.20etc.2E.20for.20relations/near/562253802\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Do you know why is this in CSLib instead of Mathlib?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Because this stuff is not really taught in mathematics departments but is bread and butter in theoretical computer science?</p>",
        "id": 562257137,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1765045324
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"646655\">Iván Renison</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Confluent.2C.20Church-Rosser.2C.20diamond.2C.20etc.2E.20for.20relations/near/562253802\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Do you know why is this in CSLib instead of Mathlib? Considering that some lemmas in Mathlib (like  <code>Relation.church_rosser</code>) are essentially using them, it is surprising for me that it is not in Mathlib</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think you should be asking the opposite question; why is <code>Relation.church_rosser</code> in Mathlib and not CSLib? CSLib didn't exist <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib3/commit/48485a2e6ef3554a2c619f8437017bccde201659\">7 years ago</a>. Though <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=FreeGroup.Red.church_rosser#doc\">docs#FreeGroup.Red.church_rosser</a> makes the cs/math boundary here a bit blurry</p>",
        "id": 562257662,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1765045912
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, this kind of stuff feels more on the boundary (because whilst mathematicians tend not to talk about SKI stuff they certainly talk about free groups).</p>",
        "id": 562258018,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1765046317
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, there are grey areas. Sometimes we prove small lemmas in CSLib that we then upstream to Mathlib. Others things like automata exist already in Mathlib, but are being extended further in CSLib. There have been discussions previously on this, but the library is new and there is no rush to move things. If maintainers feel anything should move up/downstream, please always feel free to reach out!</p>",
        "id": 562259228,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Henson",
        "timestamp": 1765047684
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay, I understand</p>",
        "id": 562259805,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1765048276
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I have another question: Are there definitions for normal forms and normalizing relations? (for an arbitrary relation)</p>",
        "id": 562259807,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1765048277
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't believe so, and this would be a welcome contribution to CSLib. Any particular reference you're working from?</p>",
        "id": 562260256,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Henson",
        "timestamp": 1765048729
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(FWIW I really like this reference - <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNwzBl6BGLwOKBFVbvp-GFjAA_ESZ--q4\">https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNwzBl6BGLwOKBFVbvp-GFjAA_ESZ--q4</a>)</p>",
        "id": 562260512,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1765049031
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"933054\">Snir Broshi</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Confluent.2C.20Church-Rosser.2C.20diamond.2C.20etc.2E.20for.20relations/near/562260512\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>(FWIW I really like this reference - <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNwzBl6BGLwOKBFVbvp-GFjAA_ESZ--q4\">https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNwzBl6BGLwOKBFVbvp-GFjAA_ESZ--q4</a>)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This seems to be particular to lambda calculi?</p>",
        "id": 562261007,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Henson",
        "timestamp": 1765049493
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"687698\">Chris Henson</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Confluent.2C.20Church-Rosser.2C.20diamond.2C.20etc.2E.20for.20relations/near/562260256\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Any particular reference you're working from?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>With my professor <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"636485\">@Miguel Pagano</span> we are exploring if it is feasible to formalize an alternative proof of the Fundamental Theorem of Arithmetic.<br>\nThe idea is for each <code>n ∈ ℕ</code> to represent it as an infinite list with finte support, <code>f : ℕ →₀ ℕ</code>, where <code>f</code> represents <code>∑ i ∈ f.support, i ^ (f i)</code>. Over that representation the idea is to define a relation that reduces the representation to a representation where the support is only prime numbers, and show that this relation is confluent and the normal forms are the prime factorizations.<br>\nThis is what I have so far (I only started today, so I'm figuring out things):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Cslib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">structure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→₀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">h₀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">h₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">toNat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">∑</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">support</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Red</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">RedStar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">Relation</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ReflTransGen</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Red</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">RedStar</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Confluence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Cslib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Confluence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NatRep</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">RedStar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 562261140,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1765049628
