    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"687698\">Chris Henson</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Confluent.2C.20Church-Rosser.2C.20diamond.2C.20etc.2E.20for.20relations/near/562261007\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This seems to be particular to lambda calculi?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes but they define {confluence, normal forms, weakly normalizing, strongly normalizing} in general</p>",
